Three months after the end of the Vida Alegre intervention, we found little difference in CES-D scores. The mean score of CES-D was 12 and 11.3 at posttest and at follow-up, respectively (see Table 3
), suggesting little change in levels of depression from T2 and T3 for the whole sample. However, the change from baseline to 3 months was significantly different, indicating the durability of the effects of the intervention (see Table 4
).
